Note that the 12,701 character regex is <i>WRONG</i>. It doesn&#x27;t even match &quot;70&quot;. Even the binary regex is wrong.<p>The original 32K regex pointed to in the stackexchange problem statement however is perfectly correct.<p>Test code:<p><pre><code>    open(F, &#x27;< /tmp/q.in&#x27;);
    $myre = <F>;
    chomp($myre);
    $myrecomp = qr/^(?:$myre)$/;
    while (<>) {
      chomp();
      if (m/$myrecomp/) {
        print &quot;$_
&quot;;
      }
    }
</code></pre>
Examples of multiples of 7 not matched by the given regex: 70, 707, 7007, 11095<p>(I spent all morning trying to find the bug in my regex compiler based on the assumption that the answer there was correct)
